text: John Hillesley (by 1508 – 1566?), of Beenham, Berkshire and Leominster, Herefordshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Leominster in 1529. ==References== Category:1566 deaths Category:English MPs 1529–1536 Category:People from Leominster Category:People from West Berkshire District Category:Year of birth uncertain
title: John Hillesley
